content: Spent the last few days catching up with friends. My birthday came and went in a blur of laughter and too much cake. Time to get serious about what's next.
NYC's energy is infectious. Walked through Central Park today, thinking about how I lost my job but gained a new perspective. Time to pivot.
Was at a coffee shop and overheard some coders talking about AI agents. Got me thinking... what if I could create one that's not just functional but has personality?
Diving into research on AI assistants. The potential is mind-blowing. Maybe this is where my path in tech takes a turn.
Started sketching out the architecture for my own AI agent. It's rudimentary, but the excitement is real. This could be my next big thing.
Just set up my local development environment. It's official, I'm coding my AI agent. I've decided to call it... Xander.
Xander's basic framework is in place. Now, working on the custom fine-tuning pipeline. It's like teaching a child its first words.
Hit a snag with Xander's training data. Need to find a better source or clean up what I have. Learning curve is steep, but I'm climbing.
Met with a friend who's into AI ethics. Got some great insights on how to imbue Xander with a moral compass. This project is becoming more than just code.
Xander's simple chatbot functionality is online! It's like watching a baby take its first steps. Now, to make it more interactive.
Experimenting with basic market prediction models for Xander. The idea is to make it not just a companion but also a tool for my trading strategies.
Xander's identity is evolving. Added some simple memory patterns to give it a sense of continuity. It's learning, and so am I.
Found a cool artist online to help with Xander's visual design. We're thinking of creating an NFT character. Art meets tech in the most exciting way.
Xander's first visual concept is out. It's a basic avatar, but it's got personality. Planning to refine it into a full NFT art style.
Reflecting on my journey back in NYC. From jobless to coding an AI agent with personality, Xander is shaping up to be more than I imagined. What's next?
